description: 90% previously unreported). Nearly half of these interactions were confirmed in differentiated neuronal cells by primary antibody immunoprecipitation and MS, with many linked to NDs and autism. We show that the SOD1-PRDX5 interaction, critical for mitochondrial redox homeostasis, can be perturbed by amyotrophic lateral sclerosis-linked variants, and establish a new functional role for ND-linked factors coupled with IκBε in NF-kB activation. Our results identify new mechanisms for MPs with direct consequences for human disease, and expands the interaction landscape of human mitochondria
